There is established within the department the   The academy shall support and train department complex area superintendents, principals, and prospective principals in areas including but not limited to:



	(1)	Becoming better leaders;
	(2)	Improving students' academic achievement, safety and well-being, and civic responsibility;
	(3)	Collaborating with the school community councils;
	(4)	Developing curriculum alignment;
	(5)	Managing school budgets; and
	(6)	Establishing partnerships with the private sector. [L 2004, c 51, §15]
